This looks like a SWT-Problem because JFace the offending JFace code looks like this:
---------------8<---------------
protected TreePath getTreePathFromItem(Item item) {
    LinkedList segments = new LinkedList();
    while (item != null) {
        Object segment = item.getData();
	Assert.isNotNull(segment); // Line 2561
	segments.addFirst(segment);
	item = getParentItem(item);
    }
    return new TreePath(segments.toArray());
}
---------------8<---------------

And getParentItem is:
---------------8<---------------
protected Item getParentItem(Item item) {
    return ((TreeItem) item).getParentItem();
}
---------------8<---------------

The only way an infinite loop can happen is when getParentItem() always returns e.g. itself instead of the parent-item but I cann't think how this could happen. The exception 

java.lang.NullPointerException
at
org.eclipse.jface.viewers.AbstractTreeViewer.getTreePathFromItem(AbstractTreeViewer.java:2561)

also looks strange to me because there can't happen a NPE in this line.
